L'ESPRIT DES LOIS

In Ireland now they all complain— And each with show of reason— That laws permit, and laws restrain,

Both loyalty and treason :

There are no laws, the peasants say, Save such as rule the breezes;

So each may go his chosen way And do whate'er he pleases.

No law there is, the priesthood teach, Save thine‚ divine expedience,—

This gospel only may one preach And look for strict obedience.

Some laws, the landlords say, were meant For beasts of chase. The same laws · Might save us, if the Government Would put in force the Game Laws.
